Senator Wofford's son speaks, to UDs

By LeeAnne Mitchell
For The Pitt News

U.S. Senator Ham's Wofford’s
son spoke to the University
Democrats last night about the
difficulties of being a
Democratic candidate right
now.

“It’s a tough time to stand up
for Democratic values right
now. People are very angry, and
they want a change — a big
change,” said David Wofford,
press secretary of his father’s re-
election campaign.

The Wofford campaign is
based on a need for government
action and change. Wofford said
his father’s campaign wants to
see a change in health care sys-
tems as well as a change in

unwarranted governmental

spending.
Wofford said Rick Santorum,
the Republican candidate, wants

to “go back” to an 80’s ‘system

..of trickle-down economics

based on tax cuts for the
wealthy and increased defense
spending.

“[The Wofford campaign]
wants a government that will be
there for the people when they
need us. We want to see a major
decrease in discretionary spend-
ing. There has been a reduction
of 200,000 federal employees,
and the budget deﬁcit has gone
down three years in a row. Why
change that now?” Wofford
asked.

Wofford said Santorum wants
to implement a health care plan
that will only benefit the
“healthy, wealthy and young.”
This plan is an IRA-type invest-
ment plan where people put into
an accotlit to draw from when
they become ill.

Wofford said that this type of
plan is “ridiculous” and asked,

“Where are non-wealthy pwple

V going to come up with the

money to put into this account?”
His father supports a plan of
universal coverage health care.

“[Rick Santorum] is a guy
who is dangerous to the welfare
of this state. He talks out of both
sides of his mouth and says
what people want to hear,”
Wofford said.

